{{Further|Non-cooperation movement (2024)}}
Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina proposed peaceful talks with the protesters, saying,
{{Cquote
| quote = "The doors of Ganabhaban are open. I want to sit with the quota protesters and listen to them. I do not want conflict."
| author = Sheikh Hasina
}}
However, in the afternoon, central coordinator Nahid Islam announced that they had no plans to negotiate with the government. He stated:{{Cquote
| quote = When we were in Detective Branch|DB custody, we were offered to sit in talks with the Prime Minister. But we protested against this proposal by going on a hunger strike in DB custody.
| author = 
}}
